### Example 4 (Positive): kref_get_unless_zero — conditional get-wrapper
Code:
```c
static inline int __must_check kref_get_unless_zero(struct kref *kref)
{{
	return refcount_add_not_zero(1, &kref->refcount);
}}
```
Callee Info: None available.

Expected output:
```json
{{
  "need_more_info": false,
  "is_wrapper": true,
  "passes_critical_variable": true,
  "purity": "high",
  "reason": "Pure get-wrapper that conditionally acquires a reference only if the refcount is non-zero. Primary purpose is entirely refcount management.",
  "conditionality": "conditional_on_nonzero",
  "must_check": true,
  "retry_on_failure": false,
  "retry_reason": "Returns 0 if refcount was zero — the object is already dead/dying. Retrying will not revive the object.",
  "contract_summary": "Conditional get-wrapper: acquires a kref reference ONLY if the refcount is non-zero (object is still alive). Returns 0 on failure — caller MUST check the return value. If 0 is returned, the object is dead/dying and must not be used."
}}
```

### Example 5 (Positive): kref_init — a set-wrapper
Code:
```c
static inline void kref_init(struct kref *kref)
{{
	refcount_set(&kref->refcount, 1);
}}
```
Callee Info: None available.

Expected output:
```json
{{
  "need_more_info": false,
  "is_wrapper": true,
  "passes_critical_variable": true,
  "purity": "high",
  "reason": "Primary purpose is to initialize the kref refcount to 1 via refcount_set. Pure set-wrapper — the caller MUST pair with a kref_put to release the reference. The set establishes the initial reference.",
  "conditionality": "unconditional",
  "must_check": false,
  "retry_on_failure": false,
  "retry_reason": "refcount_set is unconditional and always succeeds — no failure path exists, no retry needed.",
  "contract_summary": "Set-wrapper: initializes a kref to 1 (the initial reference). Called after object allocation to establish the first reference. Caller must pair every kref_init with exactly one kref_put when the object is no longer needed. This is the 'birth' point of the reference-count lifecycle."
}}
```

